  <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab>
                        <title>
                            <supplied reason="lost">Genesis 1</supplied>
                        </title>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                        <l n="1"><seg type="commented" corresp="#Gen-001-seg001_trl" />
                            <emph>In the beginning, God created the heavens and the earth.</emph>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            <addSpan spanTo="#Gen-001-add001_trl" />
                            <emph>In the very beginning God created the heaven and</emph>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            the earth. </l>
                        <l n="2">
                            <emph>And the earth was</emph>
                            <supplied reason="lost">desolated</supplied>,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            <emph>and void, and darkness was over the face of the deep.</emph>
                            <supplied reason="lost">And</supplied>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            <emph>the wind of God was hovering over the face</emph>
                            <supplied reason="lost">of</supplied>
                            <emph>the waters.</emph>
                        </l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                        <l n="3">
                            <emph>And God said, ‘Let there be light,’ and there was light.</emph>
                        </l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                        <l n="4">
                            <emph>And God saw the light, that it was good. And</emph>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            <emph>God separated between the light and the</emph>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             darkness. </l>
                        <l n="5">
                            <emph>And God called the light Day, and</emph>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            <emph>called the darkness Night. And there was evening and there
                                was</emph>
                            <supplied reason="lost">morning</supplied>:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            <emph>first</emph>
                            <ref n="1" target="#Gen-001-fn1_trl" type="noteAnchor" />
                            <emph> day.</emph>
                        </l>
                        <l n="6">
                            <emph>And God said, ‘Let there be</emph>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            <emph>a firmament in the midst of the waters, and let it divide</emph>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             water from water.’ </l>
                        <l n="7">
                            <emph>And God made</emph>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            <emph>the firmament, and separated between the waters which were</emph>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            <emph>under the firmament and the waters which were above:</emph>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             and it was so. </l>
                        <l n="8">
                            <emph>And God called the firmament</emph>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            <emph>Skies. And there was evening and there was morning: a second
                                day.</emph>
                        </l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                        <l n="9">
                            <emph>And God said, ‘Let the waters be gathered together</emph>
                            <milestone unit="page" n="2v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            <emph>under the heaven into one place, and let the dry land
                                appear.</emph>’
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             And it was so. </l>
                        <l n="10">
                            <emph>And God called the dry</emph>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            <emph>land Earth, and the gathering together of the waters he called
                                Seas.</emph>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             And God saw that it was good. </l>
                        <l n="11">
                            <emph>And God said,</emph>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             ‘<emph>Let the earth make plants grow, plants yielding seed,</emph>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            <emph>and the fruit tree making fruit, in which is their seed, according
                                to its kind,</emph>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            <emph>on the earth.’ And it was so.</emph>
                        </l>
                        <l n="12">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            <emph>And the earth brought forth plants, plants yielding seed</emph>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            <emph>according to their kind, and trees making fruit, in which is their
                                seed,</emph>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             according to its kind. And God saw that it was good. </l>
                        <l n="13">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             And there was evening and there was morning: a third day. </l>
                        <l n="14">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            <emph>And God said, ‘Let there be lights in the firmament of the</emph>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            <emph>skies to distinguish between the day and</emph>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            <emph>the night. And let them be for signs, and for appointed
                                times,</emph>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            <emph>and for days, and for years.</emph>
                        </l>
                        <l n="15">
                            <emph>And let them be for lights</emph>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            <emph>in the firmament of the skies to give light on the earth.</emph>’
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             And it was so. </l>
                        <l n="16">
                            <emph> And God made</emph>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            <emph>two great lights: the great light</emph>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            <emph>to rule the day, and the small light</emph>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             to rule the night, and the stars. </l>
                        <l n="17">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            <emph>And God set them in the firmament of the skies to give
                                light</emph>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="22" />
                            <emph>on the earth,</emph><anchor type="addSpan"
                                xml:id="Gen-001-add001_trl" /><anchor type="commented"
                                xml:id="Gen-001-seg001_trl" /><ref n="2" target="#Gen-001-fn2_trl"
                                type="noteAnchor" />
                        </l>
                        <milestone unit="page" n="3r" />
                        <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                        <l n="18"> And to rule in day time and at night <supplied reason="lost">and
                                to separate</supplied>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             the light from the <supplied reason="lost">darkness. And</supplied>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             God saw that it was good. </l>
                        <l n="19"> And there was
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             evening and there was morning and the fourth day. </l>
                        <l n="20"> And <supplied reason="lost">God said</supplied>,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             ‘Let the waters produce the swarms of living creatures and let
                                <supplied reason="lost">birds</supplied>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            <supplied reason="lost">fly</supplied> above the earth in the near
                            firmament of the skies.’ </l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                        <l n="21"> And God created <supplied reason="lost">the great</supplied> sea
                            creatures
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             and every living creature that moves <supplied reason="lost"
                                >which</supplied>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            the waters <supplied reason="lost">produced</supplied>, according to
                            their kinds, and every <supplied reason="lost">winged bird</supplied>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             according to its kind: and God saw that it was good. </l>
                        <l n="22"> And God <supplied reason="lost">blessed</supplied>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             them, saying, ‘Spread, and multiply, and <supplied reason="lost"
                                >fill</supplied>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             the waters in the seas and let birds <supplied reason="lost"
                                >multiply</supplied>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            in the earth’. </l>
                        <l n="23"> And there was evening and there was morning: the fifth
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             day. </l>
                        <l n="24"> And God said, ‘Let the earth bring forth <supplied reason="lost"
                                >living</supplied>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             beings according to their kind, livestock, and creeping animals, and
                            the wild animals of the earth according to their kind.’
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             And it was so. </l>
                        <l n="25"> And God created the <supplied reason="lost">wild
                                animals</supplied> of <supplied reason="lost">the</supplied>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             earth according to their kind and the livestock according to their
                            kinds and every
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             creeping animal of the earth: and God saw that it was good. </l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                        <l n="26"> And God said, ‘Let us create man <supplied reason="lost"
                                >in</supplied> our appearance,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             after our likeness and let them rule over the fish of <supplied
                                reason="lost">the sea</supplied>,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             and the birds of the skies, and the livestock, and over all <supplied
                                reason="lost">the</supplied>
                            <milestone unit="page" n="3v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            <supplied reason="lost">earth</supplied> , and over the creeping animals
                            that move on the earth’. </l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                        <l n="27"> So God created man in his appearance,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             in the image of angels he created him: he created them male and female. </l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                        <l n="28"> And God blessed them and God said to them
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             ‘Spread and multiply and fill the earth,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             and subdue it, and rule over the fish of the sea
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             and over the birds of the skies and over every living thing that moves
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             on the earth’. </l>
                        <l n="29"> And God said, ‘Lo,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             I have given you every plant bearing seed, which
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             is on the face of all the earth, and every tree, which
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             has seeds bearing fruit trees; to you it shall be for food. </l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                        <l n="30"> And to every wild animal of the earth, and to every bird of the
                            skies,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             and to everything that moves on the earth, wherein there is a living
                            being,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             |I have given| all the green of plants for food.’ And it was so. </l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                        <l n="31"> And God saw everything that he had created, and,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             lo, it was very good; and there was evening and there was morning: the
                            sixth
                            <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Gen001-P3v-L17_trl" n="17"
                                next="ADub.III.73.001.002.trl.xml#Gen002-P3v-L17_trl" />
                             day. </l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app>
                        <note xml:id="Gen-001-fn1_trl" type="footnote">Lit. ‘one’.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Gen-001-fn2_trl" type="footnote">Inserted by another hand in
                            South-Western Karaim.</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
